This paper deals with the problem of pattern search on labeled graphs, which is a fundamental problem in many areas of computer science such as recommendation systems, social network analysis, and semantic search. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for any-k ranking, which is a practical solution to the problem of selecting value k. The paper also focuses on acyclic patterns over arbitrary labeled graphs, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of selective constraints on labels and the fact that users often explore only a fraction of the top-ranked results, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
